 Urgie - Ugie Detectives have appealed to the public to assist them in the identification of a body of an unknown male person, suspected to be between the ages of 30 and 35 years. "The body was found on 07 June 2020 next to Nikina Old Police Station in the Tsolo area," said police spokesperson, Captain Ursula Roelofse. "On further investigation, it was found that the deceased sustained upper body bruises. "The deceased is dark in complexion and about 1,5m tall and has a slender built." Captain Roelofse said that anyone, who can assist the Ugie Detectives in identifying the person or shed light on what could have transpired, is urged to contact Sergeant Ngwenze at office no 045-933 1193 or cellphone 078 534 9329 / 078 330 3865. "Information can also be shared at any nearest police station or SAPS Crime Stop 08600 10111," she said. "All shared information will be treated with strict confidentiality and callers can remain anonymous." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 